Suspect Drug: Mucinex Unspecified Liquid.
Dosing: 5ml every 4 hours.
Case reference number US-RB-082557-16 is a spontaneous case report sent by a consumer which refers to a 
male aged 4 years.
Print Time: 15-JUL-2016 02:45 PM If a field is blank, there is no data for that field Page 203 of 250
FDA - Adverse Event Reporting System (FAERS) 
FOIA Case Report Information
It was reported by patient s father that from 22-FEB-2016 he began giving his 4 year old son Mucinex Unspecified 
Liquid, 5 ml, frequency every 4 hours, route, indication, stop date and duration were all unknown. The reporter 
stated that from 23-FEB-2016 his son started to experience excitably as well as manic behaviours. Reporter also 
stated that his son was also experiencing some aggression as well, to the family cat. Reporter sated that his son 
was normally a timid child. Reporter wanted to know how long would it take for the medicine to get out of his 
system. The patient last took the product on 25-FEB-2016. At the time of reporting action taken with drug was 
unknown and outcome of events was not recovered.
The case was deemed serious because it was classed as medically significant due to mania and agitation.
No further information was available at the time of report.
Case assessment for Mucinex Unspecified Liquid is as follows:
The reported serious assessment has not been provided, case relatedness is Possible.
The company's assessment is Serious with a relatedness of Possible and Unknown.
Case outcome: Not Recovered / Not Resolved.